scratcher
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:bed; a (makeshift) bed, bunk, sleeping bag;(also phrase HIT THE SCRATCHER = hit the sack)
Origin:[none]
Register: informal
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1940 Les Cleveland espec. trampers', but also WW2 in 2NZEF (? from fern beds in tramping huts) --ca1945-48 popular in Weir House, VUW.
